Esther 10-1 <pb/>King Ahasuerus imposed tax on the land and on <f>ⓐ</f>the coastlands of the sea.
Esther 10-2 And all the acts of his power and might, and the full account of the high honor of Mordecai, <f>ⓑ</f>to which the king advanced him, are they not written in <f>ⓒ</f>the Book of the Chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia?
Esther 10-3 For Mordecai the Jew was <f>ⓓ</f>second in rank to King Ahasuerus, and he was great among the Jews and popular with the multitude of his brothers, for he <f>ⓔ</f>sought the welfare of his people and spoke peace to all his people.